Comprehensive Sales Data Science Project Report

Executive Summary

This capstone project demonstrates an end-to-end data science workflow using sales data. The dataset includes columns for Date, Product, Quantity, Price, Customer_ID, Region, and Total_Sales. The project’s objective was to forecast sales, identify business insights, and deploy a predictive application. Deliverables include technical documentation, a business report, a presentation, and a deployed application.

Problem Statement

Businesses often struggle with predicting sales trends and optimizing inventory. This project aims to build a machine learning model to forecast sales and provide actionable recommendations for inventory planning and marketing strategies.

Methodology

Data Preprocessing

Converted Date to datetime format.

Engineered features: Month, Year, Revenue.

Encoded categorical variables (Product, Region, Customer_ID).

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Visualized sales trends over time.

Compared regional performance.

Identified correlations between discounts, price, and sales.

Model Development

Trained Random Forest Regressor for sales prediction.

Evaluated using R² and RMSE metrics.

Extracted feature importance to identify key drivers of sales.

Deployment

Built a Flask API (/predict endpoint) for real-time predictions.

Developed a Streamlit dashboard for interactive visualization and forecasting.

Documentation & Reporting

Technical documentation: methodology, code structure, results.

Business report: executive summary, recommendations.

Presentation slides: problem → solution → impact.

Results

Model Performance: Achieved strong predictive accuracy with Random Forest.

Key Insights:

Region X contributes ~40% of total revenue.

Discounts increase sales volume by ~25%.

Seasonality (holiday months) strongly influences demand.

Recommendations

Focus marketing campaigns in high-performing regions.

Adjust inventory planning based on seasonal demand.

Use discount strategies strategically to boost sales.

Deliverables

Technical Documentation: Detailed methodology and code structure.

Business Report: Executive summary and actionable recommendations.

Presentation Deck: 10–15 slides covering workflow and insights.

Deployed Application: Flask API + Streamlit dashboard.

GitHub Repository: Organized structure with README, notebooks, and source code.

Conclusion

This project successfully demonstrates a complete data science workflow applied to sales forecasting. It provides both technical depth and business relevance, making it a strong portfolio piece for data science career preparation.
